Professor of Economics and Director of Academic Planning, Caleb University Imota, Lagos, Olumuyiwa Owolabi Olamade, will on Thursday, June 15, 2023, present the institution’s 5th Inaugural Lecture Series. A statement by Olawale Adekoya, the institution’s Information, Media and Publication Specialist, said the lecture is titled: “Manufacturing Prosperity and Services of the Future: Re-igniting Nigeria’s Engine of Growth.” Speaking on the inaugural lecture, the Vice-Chancellor, Professor Nosa Owens-Ibie, who chairs the event, said: “With a growing number of distinguished professors emerging from the unique Caleb University crucible, we are commencing with Prof. Olumuyiwa Olamade’s deep and stylishly introduced inaugural lecture, a series of impactful lectures, which would be speaking to the nuances of the Nigerian and global knowledge industry.” Prof. Olamade, the inaugural lecturer, who doubles as the institution’s Dean of Students Affairs, is a member of the Chartered Institute of Logistics and Transport in the United Kingdom. He holds a Bachelor of Science (B.Sc.) in Economics, and a Master of Science (M.Sc.) in International Economics with a distinction from the University of Ibadan. The technology puzzle in international trade aroused his insatiable interest in Technology Management, which culminated in his second Master of Science (M.Sc.) degrees in Technology & Industrialization, and Technology Management, as well as a Doctorate (P.hD) in Technology Management from Obafemi Awolowo University (OAU) in 2007.